"menu.engine.howto" = "How to Choose an Engine";
"engine.howto.message" = "• Apple Speech\nBest for: everyday dictation, stable networks, and prioritizing recognition accuracy.\nStrengths: well integrated with macOS, fast streaming results, and usually broader language support.\nTradeoffs: normally depends on network/system services; audio may be processed by Apple's online service; weak network or Apple service issues can reduce reliability.\n\n• SherpaOnnx\nBest for: privacy-focused use, offline environments, or avoiding Apple Speech services.\nStrengths: fully local, no internet required, and audio is not sent to third parties.\nTradeoffs: requires model and runtime files; current models may be weaker than Apple Speech in language coverage, accuracy, punctuation, and proper-noun recognition; uses more local resources.\n\n• Apple Force Offline\nBest for: keeping the Apple Speech experience while avoiding cloud processing as much as possible.\nTradeoffs: some languages are unsupported; accuracy may drop; recognition may fail if local speech assets are missing; still limited by Apple's Speech framework.\n\nRecommendation: choose Apple for accuracy; choose SherpaOnnx for privacy and fully offline use; enable Apple Force Offline if you want Apple Speech but prefer local processing.";

